# IAM GitHub — SSH Git Workflow for Agents

**PTY runtime has no `gh` CLI and no GitHub auth helper.** OAuth MCP and in-app agents must use **terminal git over SSH** for commits, new files, scaffolds, and multi-file changes.

## Default workflow (Sam / `ws_inneranimalmedia`)

1. **Discover** with `agentsam_github_*` **read** tools (list repos, read file, get tree, list branches).
2. **Mutate** with `agentsam_terminal_run` / `agentsam_terminal_remote` in the workspace root (`cd` is applied automatically).
3. Use **SSH remotes**, not HTTPS — keys are on the Mac/GCP PTY host (`~/.ssh/config`).

| Repo | SSH remote |
|------|------------|
| `SamPrimeaux/inneranimalmedia` | `git@github.com:SamPrimeaux/inneranimalmedia.git` |
| `SamPrimeaux/agentsam-cms-editor` | `git@github.com:SamPrimeaux/agentsam-cms-editor.git` |
| `SamPrimeaux/inneranimalmedia-mcp-server` | `git@github.com-inneranimal-mcp:SamPrimeaux/inneranimalmedia-mcp-server.git` |

SSH host aliases on the PTY machine: `github.com` (default), `github-inneranimal`, `github.com-inneranimal-mcp`, `github.com-agentsam`.

## When to use GitHub API write tools

| Use API | Use terminal git |
|---------|------------------|
| Single-line fix to **existing** file when you already have `sha` | **New files**, new directories, scaffolds |
| Create PR / issue / comment after branch exists | Multi-file refactors, `npm init`, generated assets |
| Read/search/list operations | `git clone`, `git add`, `git commit`, `git push` |

**Do not** adapt scaffolds by stuffing everything into one existing file because write tools failed — clone or mkdir locally and commit properly.

## Terminal patterns (no `gh`)

```bash
# verify SSH (non-fatal if rate-limited)
ssh -T git@github.com

# clone into workspace (example)
git clone git@github.com:SamPrimeaux/REPO.git ../REPO

# new file + commit
install -d src/pages
printf '%s\n' '...' > src/pages/Contact.jsx
git add src/pages/Contact.jsx
git commit -m "feat: add contact page"
git push origin HEAD
```

## GitHub Contents API pitfalls

- `update_file` **requires** `sha`; empty string ≠ missing — omit `sha` for create.
- OAuth MCP `agentsam_github_create_file` must not route to `update_file`.
- Prefer git for anything that would need more than one Contents API call.

